transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hi, this is Jay Maslin.

Speaker 1: I had called yesterday about cancelling subscription,

Speaker 2: and I just sent an e-mail asking for confirmation,

Speaker 1: and they responded to say,

Speaker 2: call and request that you notify the pharmacy to hold any refills.

Speaker 1: So you want to hold a refill to reorder as needed, or you want to cancel?

Speaker 2: No, no, no, no, no. I'm canceling.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Now, I heard hold. That's why I'm asking question.

Speaker 1: I'm not trying to hold you or anything like that.

Speaker 2: I'm just asking question because I kind of heard something.

Speaker 1: That's the reason why.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: So you say you need an e-mail confirming the confirmation?

Speaker 2: Yes, if I could, please.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Let me send a request.

Speaker 1: I don't send e-mails, but I have somebody who does that.

Speaker 2: So I'm going to send a request right now for you.

Speaker 1: Give me one moment.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Mr. Maslin?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, you will receive an e-mail, okay?

Speaker 2: I'll send a request for you.

Speaker 1: You're going to have an e-mail stating that everything has been canceled, okay?

Speaker 2: Your account is canceled here.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Terrific.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: You too.
